<h1>Problem 451 - 2011 Iran TST, P1 of 12, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>In acute triangle \(ABC\), \(\angle B\) is greater than \(\angle C\). Let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(\overline{BC}\) and let \(E\) and \(F\) be the feet of the altitudes from \(B\) and \(C\), respectively. Let \(K\) and \(L\) be the midpoints of \(\overline{ME}\) and \(\overline{MF}\), respectively, and let \(T\) be on line \(KL\) such that \(\overline{TA} \parallel \overline{BC}\). Prove that \(TA = TM\).</p>
